Layer beef, onion, beans and pepper in 3 1/2- to 4-quart slow cooker. Pour simmer sauce into slow cooker; do not stir. Cover and cook on Low 8 to 10 hours, or on High 4 to 5 hours, or until beef is tender. Meanwhile, microwave rice as directed on package. Just before serving, stir peas into stew. Cover and heat until peas are hot. Spoon stew over rice and sprinkle with pistachios.